{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti chapter 12 does not specify a particular number of hells.** \n\nInstead, it refers to sinners obtaining \"dreadful hells\" (e.g., Mn_12.54, 12.75) as part of the consequences of karma before rebirth.[^1] Specific hells named as examples include Tāmisra (and \"the others\"), Asipatravana (and \"the like\"), and Kumbhīpāka.[^2] No exhaustive list or total count (such as the 21 hells referenced in chapter 4)[^3] appears here; the focus is on the general cycle of punishment, rebirth, and purification rather than enumerating hells.\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, ch. 12, [full chapter](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, ch. 12, [p-074f6e](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-074f6e) (Mn_12.75–76).\n\n[^3]: Manusmṛti, ch. 4, [p-8b8ea4](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/04/translation/#p-8b8ea4) (Mn_4.87; outside the queried chapter).",
